<br>
The fact that it was unseen as a possibility until we had the two named mezzed and ready to be killed (in order to start the RZtWL event) is however, a bit much.<br>
<br>
I'd be a liar if I said I wasn't devastated by what happened.  But I'm just as much to blame for feeling that way.  Having participated in so many reso events over the past month or so, with no other wants/needs than to be part of something &quot;bigger&quot;, I allowed myself to think that my own meager contributions were at least not totally un-noticed.  We all say &quot;gratz&quot; to friends and guildies all the time, because we all know how important it is to feel appreciated.  To feel like we accomplished something other than spending another X hours in front of the timesink.  I should have known better.  I shouldn't have allowed myself to think that in the eyes of this guild, I was anything more than a temporary fix, to be discarded as easily as yesterdays newspaper.  <br>
<br>
As with everything else in life, I always learn the hard way.<br>
<br>
It is with great sadness, and resolute determination, that I say; That was the last time I will participate in anything reso sponsored.<br>
<br>
Best wishes Resolution in your future endeavors.<br>
