<br>
Let me ask you this.  Have you ever had a free lunch?  At what point should I, one of the members of this guild, one of the people who worked my ass off to get the guild to where it is, be forced to give up a flag for an encounter that I've likely attempted ten times or more, to a guest who turns up ONCE?  Is that fair?  If I turn up for the encounter, and if I've had a far, far bigger impact on Resolution than you have, why should you get the flag over me?  Is that not selfishness on your part?<br>
<br>
It's nothing to do with selfishness.  It's reward.  It's reward for those who faithfully turn up night after night to help us out.  It's the risk you take in coming along.  If you're coming along, you should be coming with a view to either seeing what the guild is like, or as an invited guest who wants to enjoy themselves and do something they normally wouldn't do.  You come along expecting a flag.  You know what?  The first times I fought that encounter, be it Rallos Zek or Bertoxxulous, I never expected a flag.  I expected to get my arse handed to me.  I usually did.  I almost always did.  I remember sitting through two hours of Bertox ring and getting our arses handed to us by a stray rampage.<br>
<br>
However, if a raid with more than seventy two people turns up, including guests and members, we are obviously going to prioritize our own damn flock for the flags.  Where's the insanity in that?<br>
<br>
You help Resolution and chances are, we will do bend ourselves over fucking backwards to help you back.  You help us kill Rallos Zek, you miss the flag, we apologize.  You almost certainly get it next time.  That's the way it works.  I had to do CoD High Priest about ten times to get the entire guild flagged.  However, you turn up to one raid, guest status, and expect a flag over one of our members the first time we win an encounter?  Are you honestly being sane?  The ONLY people who have that priviledge are those who have helped us in the past.  Witness Nakath and Esoteric Order (barring one lousy decision that the full details of I am not sure), witness Telorea.  We're taking Nakath and his guild to the elementals.  Probably Telorea too if she wishes to come.<br>
<br>
What amuses me intensely as that Resolution often gets off it's arse to go help people with Planes wipes.  Should we go up there expecting to loot things?  Is that how it works?  I suppose we should expect payment, in platinum, for the tour of the Plane of Mischief that I personally spent twenty hours working for last time as well.<br>
<br>
